---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const siblingServices = [
  { name: "Teeth Whitening", href: "/services/cosmetic/whitening" },
  { name: "Porcelain Veneers", href: "/services/cosmetic/veneers" },
  { name: "Smile Makeovers", href: "/services/cosmetic/smile-makeovers", current: true },
  { name: "Dental Bonding", href: "/services/cosmetic/bonding" },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Smile Makeovers | Cosmetic Dentistry | Able Family Dental Lethbridge"
  description="Smile makeover consultations at Able Family Dental in Lethbridge, coordinating multiple cosmetic treatments to address individual aesthetic concerns."
>

  <!-- ============================================================
       HERO
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] relative overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Right-side image panel, desktop only -->
    <div class="hidden lg:block absolute right-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-[42%] pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true">
      <img
        src="/images/sourced/service-cosmetic-tooth-heart.jpeg"
        alt=""
        width="800"
        height="600"
        loading="eager"
        decoding="async"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-y-0 left-0 w-2/3" style="background: linear-gradient(to right, var(--color-brand-primary), transparent);"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="container-wide relative py-16 lg:py-24 lg:max-w-[64%]">
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-white mb-5" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/" class="text-white hover:text-white/80 transition-colors">Home</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <a href="/services/" class="text-white/80 hover:text-white transition-colors">Services</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <a href="/services/cosmetic/" class="text-white/80 hover:text-white transition-colors">Cosmetic</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <span class="text-white">Smile Makeovers</span>
      </nav>
      <p class="eyebrow text-white">Cosmetic Dentistry</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-5xl)] leading-tight text-white max-w-2xl">
        Smile Makeovers
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
        A smile makeover is a coordinated treatment plan that combines two or more cosmetic procedures to address a patient's specific aesthetic concerns. Every plan begins with a health assessment, ensuring that underlying dental health is sound before any cosmetic work is considered.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       MAIN CONTENT + SIDEBAR
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="section-y bg-white">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_300px] gap-12">

        <!-- LEFT: Main content -->
        <div class="space-y-10">

          <!-- Health first -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-surface-alt)] rounded-2xl p-6 border border-[var(--color-border-soft)]">
            <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-brand-accent)] flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="white" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-base text-[var(--color-brand-primary)]">Oral health comes first</h3>
                <p class="mt-1.5 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">
                  All cosmetic treatment at Able Family Dental begins with a thorough oral health assessment. Any underlying decay, gum disease, or other dental concerns are addressed before cosmetic work is planned or performed. Cosmetic procedures applied to an unhealthy foundation are unlikely to hold up well over time.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Image break -->
          <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden max-h-[700px]">
            <img
              src="/images/services/hero-cosmetic.jpg"
              alt="Shade guide used during a cosmetic dental consultation"
              width="800"
              height="450"
              loading="lazy"
              decoding="async"
              class="w-full h-auto"
            />
          </div>


          <!-- What a smile makeover is -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              What a smile makeover involves
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                A smile makeover refers to planning and coordinating multiple cosmetic treatments together, rather than addressing individual concerns in isolation. By considering the teeth, gum line, and overall appearance together, the resulting treatment plan can address several concerns in a way that is cohesive and appropriate for your specific situation.
              </p>
              <p>
                It is not a single procedure, it is a process that begins with a consultation, proceeds through any necessary health treatment, and then moves into the cosmetic phase as appropriate. The sequence and combination of treatments depend entirely on the individual patient's dental health, concerns, and goals.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- What concerns can be addressed -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              What concerns may be addressed
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Depending on the situation, a coordinated cosmetic plan may address concerns such as:
              </p>
              <ul class="mt-3 space-y-3">
                {[
                  "Tooth discolouration or staining that has not responded adequately to routine whitening",
                  "Chipped, worn, or fractured tooth surfaces",
                  "Gaps between teeth",
                  "Teeth that appear short, disproportionate, or uneven in size or shape",
                  "Mild crowding or misalignment that affects appearance",
                  "Gum line irregularities that affect the visible proportion of the teeth",
                ].map(item => (
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                    <svg class="mt-1 shrink-0 text-[var(--color-brand-accent)]" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="5 12 10 17 19 7"/></svg>
                    <span class="text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">{item}</span>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-3">
                In any given case, the extent to which these concerns can be addressed depends on the patient's dental health, the anatomy of their teeth and gums, their goals, and practical considerations including budget and timeline.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Common combinations -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              Common treatment combinations
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-5">
              {[
                {
                  title: "Whitening and bonding",
                  body: "Teeth whitening can address overall discolouration, while composite bonding can repair individual chips or close small gaps. These two treatments are often coordinated so that bonding is colour-matched to the whitened shade.",
                },
                {
                  title: "Veneers with whitening of adjacent teeth",
                  body: "If veneers are placed on some teeth, the remaining visible teeth may be whitened so that the overall appearance is consistent. Whitening is typically completed before the veneers are fabricated, so the veneer shade can be matched to the whitened teeth.",
                },
                {
                  title: "Orthodontics followed by whitening or bonding",
                  body: "In some cases, orthodontic treatment to improve alignment is a useful first step before cosmetic work, particularly when crowding or spacing affects what cosmetic treatments are practical. Whitening or bonding may then follow to address any remaining concerns.",
                },
                {
                  title: "Gum contouring with restorative or cosmetic work",
                  body: "When the gum line affects the appearance of the teeth, contouring may be considered alongside other cosmetic treatment, though gum health must be confirmed as appropriate before any soft tissue work is done.",
                },
              ].map(item => (
                <div class="rounded-2xl border border-[var(--color-border-soft)] p-6">
                  <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-[var(--color-brand-primary)]">{item.title}</h3>
                  <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">{item.body}</p>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- The consultation process -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              The consultation process
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                A smile makeover consultation at Able Family Dental begins with listening to your concerns and understanding what aspects of your smile you would like to address. We then conduct a thorough examination of your teeth, gums, and bite.
              </p>
              <p>
                From there, we discuss the options that are appropriate for your situation, including what each option involves, how long it takes, what the maintenance requirements are, how long it is likely to last, and what the costs are. We aim to give you a clear and realistic picture so you can make informed decisions.
              </p>
              <p>
                Not every concern has a single solution, and some treatments may not be suitable depending on your dental health or tooth anatomy. We will be straightforward with you about what is feasible and what trade-offs are involved. Some patients proceed with a full plan; others choose to address one or two concerns at a time. We work around your priorities and timeline.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- RIGHT: Sidebar -->
        <aside class="space-y-6">

          <!-- Book CTA card -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] rounded-2xl p-6 text-white">
            <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-white">Request a Consultation</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)]">Call us or request an appointment online, new patients welcome.</p>
            <a href="/book/" class="mt-4 btn btn-primary w-full block text-center">Book Appointment</a>
            <a href="/refer/" class="mt-2 btn btn-outline w-full block text-center">Refer Patient</a>>
            <a href="tel:+14033277202" class="mt-2 block text-center text-sm text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] hover:text-white transition-colors">403.327.7202</a>
          </div>

          <!-- Sibling services card -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-surface-cool)] rounded-2xl p-6 border border-[var(--color-border-soft)]">
            <h3 class="font-body text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">Cosmetic Services</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              {siblingServices.map(svc => (
                <li>
                  {svc.current ? (
                    <span class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-brand-accent)]">
                      <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-brand-accent)] shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                      {svc.name}
                    </span>
                  ) : (
                    <a href={svc.href} class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] hover:text-[var(--color-brand-accent)] transition-colors">
                      <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-border-soft)] shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                      {svc.name}
                    </a>
                  )}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>

        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       CTA BAND
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] py-16 text-center overflow-hidden relative">
    <svg class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full pointer-events-none" viewBox="0 0 1440 160" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true">
      <path d="M0 60 C 240 20, 480 100, 720 60 C 960 20, 1200 100, 1440 60 L1440 160 L0 160 Z" fill="rgba(255,255,255,0.03)"/>
    </svg>
    <div class="relative container-wide">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-4xl)] text-white leading-tight">Ready to discuss your options?</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] text-lg max-w-xl mx-auto">Call <a href="tel:+14033277202" class="text-white font-semibold hover:text-[var(--color-brand-accent-soft)] transition-colors">403.327.7202</a> or book a consultation.</p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/book/" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Book Appointment</a>
        <a href="/refer/" class="btn btn-lg border border-white/30 text-white hover:bg-white/10 transition-colors">Refer Patient</a>>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-lg border border-white/30 text-white hover:bg-white/10 transition-colors">Contact Us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
